k. TikTok
We have embedded the TikTok Pixel and comparable functions of the TikTok video platform on our pages. idealo processes your data in joint responsibility with TikTok (TikTok Information Technologies UK Limited, WeWork, 125 Kingsway, London, WC2B 6NH, England and TikTok Technology Limited, 10 Earlsfort Terrace, Dublin, D02 T380, Ireland). If you also have a user account for the TikTok video platform and are logged in there or log in there at a later time, TikTok can directly assign your visit to our website and the event data collected to this user account. If you visit websites or mobile applications of other providers that also use the TikTok pixel, TikTok can also link this information to your user account. This enables TikTok, among other things, to determine the users of a website or mobile application as a target group for the display of certain adverts on their video portal and to address them specifically ("re-targeting"). Accordingly, we use the TikTok Pixel so that our adverts on the TikTok video portal are primarily displayed to TikTok users who have already visited our website or have certain characteristics, e.g. have shown interest in certain products or topics. We can also use the pixel to record and analyse the effectiveness of our ads on the video portal for statistical and market research purposes. By using the pixel, TikTok can determine how many users clicked on an advert placed for us and were redirected to our offer (so-called "conversion measurement").
We are jointly responsible with TikTok for the collection of data via the TikTok Pixel and the transfer of the collected data to TikTok for the purpose of re-targeting and conversion measurement (measurement of the effectiveness of advertising measures) in accordance with Art. 26 GDPR (but not for the further processing of the data by TikTok). For this joint processing activity, we have concluded a special agreement with TikTok provided by TikTok. According to this agreement, idealo and TikTok are obliged to provide their users with the data protection information required under Articles 13 and 14 GDPR and, in particular, to inform them about the joint data processing. If you wish to assert your right of cancellation or your rights as a data subject under Articles 15 to 23 GDPR with regard to the joint data processing described above, TikTok acts as a joint point of contact and processes all applications to assert these rights. However, you can also contact us.
You can access the full text of our agreement with TikTok here:
https://ads.tiktok.com/i18n/official/article?aid=300871706948451871
Further information on the processing of your personal data by TikTok can be found here:
https://www.tiktok.com/legal/page/eea/privacy-policy/en
.
l. AWIN
With your consent, we use the affiliate network AWIN (AWIN AG, Stralauer Allee 2, 10245 Berlin) to record whether you have purchased a product from a member of the network after visiting our services so that we can receive remuneration for this. AWIN will not collect any personal data without your consent.
