m. Media Impact
When you visit our website, our advertising partner MI sets cookies or comparable technologies with a pseudonymous identification number (‘MI-ID’) in your browser, subject to your consent. We can read this MI-ID and add it to your user profile. We analyse your usage data to gain insights into your interests and create target group profiles. To enable MI to display personalised advertising from MI advertising partners on other websites, we and MI occasionally compare our MI-IDs, whose user profile corresponds to a specified target group criterion, and the MI-IDs available at MI.
Your MI-ID is compared by a service provider using a secure procedure (‘Data Clean Room’). For this purpose, we and MI have concluded an agreement with the service provider for order processing in accordance with Art. 28 GDPR. Only pseudonymised MI IDs are processed in the Data Clean Room. If your MI ID is present in the Data Clean Room in both our area and MI's area (‘match’), MI can use this information to display or optimise personalised advertising for MI advertising partners on other websites.
The MI-ID and target group criteria provided by us are not permanently stored in the data clean room or at MI.
Further information on data processing by Media Impact can be found at
https://www.mediaimpact.de/de/ueber-unsere-werbung/
.
MI and idealo act in joint responsibility when processing data that is processed via the MI ID for target group determination and matching. We have concluded an agreement with MI in this respect regarding joint responsibility within the meaning of Art. 26 GDPR, in which we have defined the respective responsibilities for fulfilling the obligations under the GDPR. Accordingly, we and MI are obliged to enable you to grant and revoke consent under data protection law. In addition, we are the central point of contact for you as the data subject. We will forward any data subject requests that we receive and that relate to our joint responsibility to MI for response without undue delay. Nevertheless, you can assert the rights to which you are entitled under the GDPR as a data subject both with and against us and with and against MI.
The legal basis for the data processing is Art. 6 (1) point a GDPR. You have the option to revoke the consent you have given at any time in the
privacy
settings.
